commit 837b11577979e07fab4cf848ae59ff89444a038b
Author: Matt Nichols <mnichols@twitter.com>
Date:   Mon Apr 7 13:34:58 2014 -0700

    Introduce mobile terminated add-phone module
    
    Add a reusable module for adding a phone to a signed-in user's account,
    a NSFormatter subclass for formatting and validating phone numbers, and
    UI + unit tests (respectively). Also adds an experiment to introduce
    this instead of the current MO add-phone step during the NUX for some
    users.
    
    The API currently only supports a longer verification token, used in
    this patch through a deeplink the user can tap from the text message.
    I'll push another patch to add manual entry of a shorter token once
    support for this exists.
    
    Also as a followup: fleshed out phone number formatter
    
    Jira:ACTIVATE-935
    Change-Id: I75319c4cbd5d1d17733c03ef84e0872cf99959ef

Author: Dave Schukin <dschukin@twitter.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 13 00:48:07 2014 -0700

    UIAutomation tests for #hashflags
    
    Notes:
    
    * These tests swizzle -[TFNHTTPRequest data] such that hash flags
      are added as metadata to all tweets, and thus are rendered in all tweets.
      Although they will be rendered out of ordinary order (if a user actually
      typed a given hashflag(s)), the point of this test is to make sure the rendering
      doesn't cause a crash.
    * If anyone is more familiar with Subliminal, we can certainly use more stress
      testing, as the bug (/crasher) in question usually occurred after low
      memory warnings (which we found, for that specific bug, couldn't be simulated)
    * Much of this swizzling / data manipulation code was copied directly from
      an earlier patch containing similar tests for World Cup (see
      https://gerrit.twitter.biz/#/c/38827/ ). These tests & the related code have
      since been removed, and I don't know why (my guess is, as is common
      in the land of iOS testing, is that they were breaking at some point and
      it was easiest to just comment/remove them. I don't know why the -degradedData
      method(s) had to go with them)
    * The the assertion in TFNTwitterStatus.m:2915 was originally added as a curiosity
      check, and an attempt to remove it was submitted in https://gerrit.twitter.biz/#/c/40118/1/TwitterPlatform/TwitterService/Twitter/Base/TFNTwitterStatus.m , however after
      talking w/ Kirk we decided to modify said UIAutomation tests. Today I don't have the
      patience to tweak my tests such that they satisfy this assertion that was added & has
      only been hit in the context of similar tests :)

commit b27c58cbc2e78dc180f78b7e36f2b411cd09aeed
Author: Reyner Crosby <rcrosby@twitter.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 10 16:11:53 2014 -0400

    Add New User Module
    
    This patch introduces a class to keep track of the new user state: TFNNewUserState.
    It uses this class to display a persistent module in the home timeline of any new
    user who has not followed any accounts, uploaded an avatar, or sent their first
    Tweet. This module is implemented with a TFNScrollBumpCell inserted in the top
    of the home timeline. The module provides visual feedback to the user upon step
    completion, which it knows about through TFNWizardNavigationControllerDelegate,
    T1EditProfileViewControllerDelegate and TFNTwitterCompositionDidSendNotification.
    
    Also included in this commit:
    
    Define tfn_animateWithDuration:delay:usingSpringWithDamping:initialSpringVelocity:
           options:animations:completion:
    - Fall back to EaseInOut if spring animations not supported
    
    Bug fixes for scroll bump page scrolling and state
    - Fixed an incorrect bounds check against _currentPage
        when we should be checking against the page index
        we're scrolling to
    - Fixed a case that could cause _currentPage to be
        stuck to a value of NSNotFound
    
    Scroll bump improvements
    - Added support for obtaining the view for a specific scroll bump page
    - Added completion block support to -scrollToPageAtIndex:animated:
    
    Note: this commit changes delegate behavoir. Previously, explicit page
      changes would not result in a call to -scrollBumpCell:didScrollToPageAtIndex:
      Now they do. (This is to make sure the page state tracking peformed by the
      base scroll bump table row adapter doesn't get out of sync with reality.)
    
    Change-Id: I7bed0713b45815f7c2dd7a628a997e1a55ed5fc8
    Jira: ACTIVATE-933

testBuyNowNoInventory.name: testBuyNowNoInventory
testBuyNowNoInventory.created_commit_log:
commit c7f462a7091c6de76a107eeb2a98f2e054c43c26
Author: Amer Shahnawaz <ashahnawaz@twitter.com>
Date:   Wed Jul 23 16:55:17 2014 -0700

    Couple of bug fixes + a subliminal test.
    
    1) Change when we fire the post-purchase notification to the completion handler
       of the view being dismissed and not in the subsequent block. Otherwise the
       notification will fire when we have a modal view controller and the
       notification center will wait 7 seconds before trying to fire again. This
       way we see the notification instantly. Also changed the copy on the
       notification.
    
    2) Ensure that buy now button is disabled when we initially load the page and
       enable it back only when get call to getProductInfo successfully returns
       with non-zero inventory. This uncovered another bug where we're not actually
       updating the skus we get back from getProductInfo properly. We were using the
       wrong key and not following the agreed upon approach which was we only keep
       the intersection of what we got from the card and what we got from the
       getproductinfo card.
    
     3) Includes a test that will catch #2 in the future. Also sets up functions to
        stub out getProductInfo calls for the no inventory and positive inventory case.
    
    Change-Id: I8f7b011d2f06a6ef20f1f6c45596cafd8c513092
    JIRA: COMMERCE-895, COMMERCE-1062
